text: The overwhelming majority of people in hospital with Covid have not been vaccinated.
90% of people in ICU with Covid-19 have not been vaccinated.
Only 32 vaccinated people have been hospitalised with Covid.
Unvaccinated people are not dying from Covid-19.
90% of people in hospital with Covid-19 are unvaccinated.
About 80-90% of those hospitalised with Covid-19 are unvaccinated.
As with people vaccinated against COVID-19, many people who were NOT vaccinated also experienced zero or mild symptoms.
60% of new COVID-19 patients are people who received the vaccine.
Unvaccinated, you can get COVID and have over 99% chance of survival. Get vaccinated and you can still get COVID and will still have over 99% chance of survival.
Around 20 million doses of COVID-19 vaccines remained unaccounted for as recently as January 2021.
